.TH "SHELLY" "1" "Dec 2025" "Shelly CLI" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
shelly-repl - Launch interactive REPL


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBshelly repl [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Launch an interactive REPL (Read-Eval-Print Loop) for Shelly CLI.

.PP
This provides a command-line shell where you can enter Shelly commands
without prefixing them with 'shelly'. It supports command history within
the session and provides a more interactive experience.

.PP
Available commands in REPL:
  help             Show available commands
  devices          List registered devices
  connect  Set active device for subsequent commands
  disconnect       Clear active device
  status           Show status of active device
  on               Turn on active device
  off              Turn off active device
  toggle           Toggle active device
  rpc      Execute raw RPC call on active device
  exit, quit, q    Exit the REPL

.PP
You can also run any shelly subcommand by typing it directly.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-d\fP, \fB--device\fP=""
	Default device to connect to

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for repl

.PP
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Disable interactive prompt (for scripting)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	Config file (default $HOME/.config/shelly/config.yaml)

.PP
\fB--log-categories\fP=""
	Filter logs by category (comma-separated: network,api,device,config,auth,plugin)

.PP
\fB--log-json\fP[=false]
	Output logs in JSON format

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colored output

.PP
\fB-o\fP, \fB--output\fP="table"
	Output format (table, json, yaml, template)

.PP
\fB-q\fP, \fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	Suppress non-essential output

.PP
\fB--template\fP=""
	Go template string for output (use with -o template)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=0]
	Increase verbosity (-v=info, -vv=debug, -vvv=trace)


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  # Start REPL mode
  shelly repl

  # Start with a default device
  shelly repl --device living-room

  # Example session:
  > devices
  > connect living-room
  > status
  > on
  > exit
.EE


